The paper deals with the analysis of cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of point processes and Laplace transforms suggests a focus on stochastic processes and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also discusses power control, which is a topic in multimedia systems (cs.MM) and game theory (cs.GT).
